    SwrlBuiltinStructure

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    EasySwrl
    Utilities to make it easier to write SWRL queries.
    SwrlAtom
    A SWRL atom.
    SwrlBuiltin  
    SwrlBuiltinResult
    SwrlBuiltinResult is a sum type which describes the result of a builtin call.
    SwrlBuiltinResult.Failure
    Returned to indicate that a builtin call has no solution.
    SwrlBuiltinResult.Success
    Returned to encapsulate a non-empty list of solutions for a builtin call.
    SwrlBuiltinResult.UnboundVar
    Returned to indicate that the parameters of the builtin are not instanciated enough (at least one more variable parameter should be bound to compute a result)
    SwrlBuiltinResult.Unsupported
    Returned to indicate that the builtin structure provides no implementation of the requested builtin.
    SwrlBuiltinStructure.Helper  
    SwrlBuiltinStructure.ValidBuiltinMode  
    SwrlDifferentFrom
    This SWRL predicate is true if its two arguments are different.
    SwrlParser
    Parse SWRL rules from a Model.
    SwrlQuery  
    SwrlRule  
    SwrlSameAs
    This SWRL predicate is true if its two arguments are the same.
    SwrlSerializer
    Utilities for serializing SWRL rules as RDF into a Model.
